iting room  with equipment to create media presentations and projects  Other services include the following  Research and recommend media equipment Train cadets and faculty in the use of multimedia software Assist with digital image and video projects Pinnacle  Final Cut Pro  or Premier basic assistance Photoshop  Paint Shop Pro  or MS Picture Manage basic assistance Microsoft Office  Word  Excel  PowerPoint  Publisher  basic assistance for media Angel and Smartclassroom prep for media Audio software basic assistance Dry mount and laminate materials Make transparencies Media Services will be glad to offer very basic assistance with media in web pages  HTML and Javascript  but it may be best to contact the IT department on more complicated issues  Canvas and Smartclassroom Training for Faculty  Media Services offers basic training for faculty on Canvas and Smartclassroom equipment  Services that require an operator or set up of equipment are available during regular departmental hours only  Delivery of equipment must be arranged through the user  Hours  0800 to 1630 Monday   Friday with school year 1900 to  2300 Monday   Thursday    Fall and Spring term only  Location  401 Preston Library  take the left stairwell down one level from the parade ground and Media Services will be straight ahead  Reservations  Requests for equipment or the assistance of a technician must be made 3 days in advance  by contacting Maj  Michael Brickler  540 464 7655 or use the Media Equipment Online Checkout Form VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 